sql:
SELECT COUNT(*) AS number_of_instances
FROM algorithm_instances
WHERE created_by = 0;

SELECT tot_cputime
FROM algorithm_instances
WHERE instance_id = 1;

SELECT tot_real_time
FROM algorithm_instances
ORDER BY tot_cputime DESC;

external_knowledge:
Fastest algorithm instances refer to those with the lowest total real time; 
Detailed performance metrics include time spent on decision diagrams, pricing, reducing cost fixing, relative error, global lower and upper bounds; 
Optimization settings include stabilization, alpha, pricing solver, first graph size, size after reduced costs, and optimization strategy.

sql:
SELECT MAX(tot_lb) AS max_total_lower_bound
FROM algorithm_instances
WHERE created_by = 1;

external_knowledge:
- 'most time-consuming' refers to the instance that spent the most time on build decision diagrams; 
- 'total real time' refers to the total time taken for the execution; 
- 'total time spent' refers to the total time spent on build decision diagrams, pricing, and reducing cost fixing.

sql:
SELECT instance_id
FROM algorithm_instances
WHERE tot_real_time = (SELECT MAX(tot_real_time) FROM algorithm_instances);

SELECT created_by, COUNT(*) AS num_instances
FROM algorithm_instances
GROUP BY created_by;
